File: A medical worker tests for the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - More than 2,000 new COVID-19 cases have been recorded, bringing the total number of infections to 767,679. The Department of Health also reported 58 more COVID-19 deaths. READ: All countries must get COVID-19 vaccine: Ramaphosa The COVID-19 death toll in South Africa is at 20,903. Of the 58 deaths, 28 are from the Eastern Cape, 13 from the Free State, eight from the Gauteng, and nine from the Western Cape. Recoveries in SA are at 710,099. The recovery rate now stands at 92.5-percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is